The forces of the mega strike come together
The unions of the League and the National Association of Workers' Councils will constitute, Friday, their strike commission which will be responsible for coordinating the strike of indefinite duration of Monday.
On Saturday, a general protest assembly will be held and on Monday, the day of the final vote on the law on health funds, the strike will begin.
This action will certainly cause major traffic jams because rail traffic will be almost completely stopped and the employees of BKV (public transport company) will also strike until 1pm.
The league unions will make known, Friday afternoon, the details of their strike on Monday, organized with the National Association of Workers' Councils.
The strike commission of LIGA - MOSZ will also be constituted, it will serve as coordinator of Monday's actions.
On Saturday, a general protest assembly will be held and, from Monday, the organizations joining the strike will stop work for an indefinite period if they cannot reach an agreement with the government.
This means that the date of the end of the strike, from the day of the vote in parliament on the law on health funds, is not defined.
If the National Assembly does not adopt the law on health funds, the unions will immediately withdraw the strike call.
On the other hand, if the law is passed, the strike committees will meet and decide on the follow-up.
According to Monday's agenda of the National Assembly, it is likely that the vote on the law on health funds will take place only late at night, or even at night.
Due to the strike scheduled for Monday, major traffic jams are expected: the railways will stop work for an indefinite period and during the morning part of the public transport in Budapest and more than half of the Volán companies are likely to be stopped.
At the same time, at different points of the country, half of the track will be blocked as well.
Many unions and civil organizations have joined the call for the strike, the list of these is constantly updated on the League's website.
Some organizations report striking for an indefinite period, others have declared a temporary work stoppage.
Until Thursday afternoon, the MÁV (Hungarian Railways) and the Free Union of Railway Workers (VDSZSZ) have not managed to reach an agreement on minimum services, but as the Christmas holidays approach, more and more people take the train.
According to current communications, public transport in Budapest will strike from the start of service until 1 p.m., Budapest Airport between 7 a.m. and 9 a.m., the League's Industrial Electricity and Thermal Energy Unions will strike for four hours, the Teachers' Union and the Democratic Teachers' Union have called for strikes for 2 hours and from 2 a.m. to 8 a.m. respectively.
The National Association of Doctors will strike throughout the country alternately, the Union of Health and Social Sector Employees (EDDSZ) attached to the SZEF will issue a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four demands, formulated by the League, demands that the government withdraw its proposal for health reform and submit a new conception to the social debate.
The second demand requires that the new method of calculating the pension to be introduced from next year be introduced in several stages.
The third demand is a guarantee, in terms of retirement before the legal age, which would allow the functions that deserve it to be transferred to the system before 2010.
The fourth reason for the action is the rejection by the Free Union of Railway Workers (VDSZSZ), attached to the Unions of the League, of the proposal of the Ministry of Economy and Transport concerning secondary railway lines and the expectation of another proposal.
Political Capital: Hungarian Guard has increased country risk
According to the Risk Analysis Division of Political Capital, the activity of the Hungarian Guard, formed last August with the support of Jobbik Magyarországért Mozgalom (Movement for a Better Hungary), increases the political risk of Hungary and the region in several respects.
In its "risk warning", the company points out that, in connection with the activity of the Hungarian Guard, the greatest political risk is already that "in the short term aggressive ethnic clashes may occur as a result of the aggravation of the already existing ethnic tension between the gypsy and non-gypsy population of Hungary".
The research institute added that the political strategy of the Hungarian Guard presumably aimed at provoking this situation is the main reason.
As they say, this is explained by one of the main shortcomings of Hungarian political actors: "public actors have passed on the public debate on the Roma case to representatives of radical and extreme political groupings who have based a political strategy on the dispute between Gypsies and Hungarians".
This aggravates the problem, normal dialogue becomes impossible, extremists are strengthened and aggressive conflicts are more likely, they say.
However, according to the research institute, as a result of the increased attention of the Hungarian and international media, the activity of the Hungarian Guard "has significantly deteriorated Hungary's image abroad, in particular with regard to confidence in the stability and democratic maturity of the country".
They recall that, following greater publicity given to the reorganization of radical and extreme right Hungarian groups since autumn 2006, many associations have been formed in Hungary since the summer of 2007 calling themselves "National Self-Defence Association".
"The common feature of these gatherings is that they define themselves as a civilian organization while they publicly declare the preparation of their members for defense missions (disasters, national defense, defense of order), armed if necessary, moreover, evoking the ineptitude of the police, the army, in other words the state," they added.
They pointed out that everything was happening according to the method which, based on the rancour of political society and parties, seeks to disguise different political ambitions under a civilian aspect.
The emphasis on civil character and association status therefore only serves to avoid the legal pitfalls of registering these associations in court, but they are also a political strategy.
The analysis indicates that the activity of the Hungarian Guard is a factor that also increases the risk in relation to neighbourly relations.
"In recent months, many neighbouring countries have cited the Hungarian Guard as a potential source of risk and ultranationalist political actors in some neighbouring countries wish to justify their anti-Hungarian policy by referring to the constitution of the Hungarian Guard.
This influences the political stability of the region," they added.
According to the research institute, the constitution of the Hungarian Guard is not a unique phenomenon in East Central Europe, political risks have increased throughout the region.
As they say, the functioning of the Hungarian Guard resembles, for example, the activity of the Bulgarian National Guard whose constitution was declared by the Bulgarian National Union (BNU) in August 2007.
The numerous Roma disturbances that broke out in a district of Sofia (Kraszna Poljana) led to the constitution of the Bulgarian Guard.
Taking advantage of these events, the BNU decided to form a guard saying that the objective of the organization is "national self-defense".
According to them, over the past 17 years, gypsies have "terrorized" Bulgaria but the state has remained inactive and neutral, recalls Political Capital.
They added that the initiative had provoked lively debates in Bulgarian public opinion.
As they say, the statement by some Bulgarian Roma organisations about forming their own guard as a form of resistance signals the increased risk of ethnic clashes.
The functioning of the Hungarian Guard showing similarities with that of the Bulgarian National Guard does not exclude that Hungarian Roma react to the threat in the same way by organizing their own self-defense, reads the risk warning of Political Capital.
At the telegraph agency's request for information, Attila Juhász, research director of Political Capital, said: risk analysis is one of the activities of the research institute.
As he said, their risk analysis is published annually and if events occur that could have an impact on the change in risk, they inform public opinion, as in this case, by issuing a risk warning.
The party is not marked in red everywhere
In Hungary, the law defines exactly the holidays and, around the holidays, it has become common to reorganize the working days, the number of which will decrease next year.
The holidays are not uniform in the EU and in the US either.
Hungarian legislation distinguishes between national and state holidays and rest days.
Rest days are often linked to religious holidays or important historical events.
In Hungary, we celebrate the New Year, the last day of the year that ends and the first day of the New Year are also days of rest, the latter especially so that the awakeners can rest quietly.
In addition, in a year, we have a total of eleven holidays marked in red.
March 15 is a national holiday, in commemoration of the revolution of 1848, as well as October 23, which is the commemorative day of the revolution of 1956.
On August 20, we celebrate the constitution of our state, May 1 is the feast of work and on November 1 and 2, we remember our family members and friends who have passed away.
In addition, we have two days at Easter, Pentecost and Christmas.
The days of our state, national or religious holidays rarely fall on a weekend, according to the calendar, it has become common to reorganize the working days in cases where there is only one working day before or after the holiday marked in red.
It is true that we pay the price of long weekends by working or going to school on the Saturday before the long weekend.
For many years, the Minister of Labour has ruled in a special regulation on the days of replacement of the days before or after the holidays.
The law extends to all employers and all their employees employees, to civil servants and to persons working in the public service.
However, it does not apply to service companies, institutions operating without interruption and in service, by their vocation, and also to rest days.
This year, the working days will be modified only around the end of the year holidays: from December 24, life stops almost throughout the country because according to experience the majority of people work overtime or take holidays that they have saved for these purposes to be able to spend the days between Christmas and New Year's Day at home.
Next year many holidays fall in the middle or at the end of the week, therefore there will be less change in working days compared to this year.
The calendar will be reorganized the first time around the work day to allow employees to stay at home four days in a row.
Saturday, April 25 will be a working day to have a rest day on Friday, May 2.
Another change is planned for October 23: Saturday, October 18 will be a replacement working day for Friday, October 24.
On the other hand, next year, the end of the year promises to be under the sign of holidays because from December 24, everyone will take a non-stop break even if New Year's Day falls on a Wednesday.
Six trivial things that can annoy colleagues terribly
Emails we forget to send, voice messages we never receive, innocent lies that annoy us almost more: these are things that "embellish" the daily life of a workplace.
The question is whether we get used to these troubles or take up the challenge and consciously avoid ambiguous situations, causing trouble for others.
Examples.
"Excuse me, I forgot to tell you they called you from the marketing department," says a colleague.
That you missed an appointment?
At best he's sorry and tries to fix things by calling the marketing department to tell them he forgot to get the message across (this is the least common solution).
In the majority of cases, the thing is arranged with an apology.
Before having painful explanations, it is useful to think about how you can cause unpleasant moments to your colleagues and to make efforts to avoid them.
Are you borrowing something that doesn't belong to you?
There's nothing more annoying than wanting to grab a folder, an office tool or the phone and you can't find them anywhere.
Do you remember that the day before you put the stapler on the desk but it disappeared the next morning?
Do you accidentally find your pen that you thought was lost on your colleague's desk?
Do not take anything from your colleagues without asking otherwise they are right to be angry with you for having stolen their property.
Do not bring envelopes, post-it notes in your pocket because it can be annoying that there are no more and that you need them right away.
Do you chat about the privacy of colleagues?
There are no good ways to stop gossip that is spreading.
Who did what, with whom?
Where and why?
Don't tell everyone your information (assumptions) about your colleagues' private lives!
If a colleague shares their intimate secrets with you, don't abuse their trust!
Bury the shared information in you and do not discuss it with your colleagues in his absence even if your colleagues are also aware.
Do you declare yourself sick for no reason?
When you call the office and declare yourself sick under the pretext of a heartbreaking headache because you feel bad or you feel you need rest that day, think about the fact that your work, your urgent business, your missions must be carried out by someone else in your place.
Don't make trouble for your colleagues!
If you know in advance that the next day you will not go to work or that something may happen that would force you to stay at home, do not forget to warn your boss and your colleagues so that they are not surprised by your absence the next day.
Humming, snickering, phone
You immerse yourself in your work but the sneer of your colleagues brutally tears you away?
You have unwittingly become a witness to a telephone discussion that you would have been better off not listening?
Do not disturb your colleagues with humming, humming, talking aloud (which you lead over their head), kicks, swear words or discontent expressed aloud.
They can be disturbing even if your colleagues are not immersed in a project (writing, design, organization).
Are you accusing others of a foul?
If your work is not done by the deadline, you forget to send a mail or an important message, do not blame anyone for this oversight!
Don't blame it on the possible chaos in the office or your noisy colleagues!
Recognize it if you made a mistake and if it presented inconvenience to others, repair the fault!
Ask how you could make amends for your mistake, fix the negligence!
Do you feel too at home in the office?
Putting a jogging and slippers is comfortable at home but they are not suitable for the office!
Do not put on comfortable jogging even if your function allows it!
Do not be neglected, respect your colleagues and yourself by dressing properly, and if your function requires it by putting on pretty and elegant clothes, to go to work!
