600 thousand people failed to renew their driver's license on time
Six hundred thousand drivers allowed the deadline to expire and failed to renew their old driving licences, which expire at the end of the year.
This is the last day that people can still apply for renewal, so the authorities are in a position to issue them a new licence before the end of the year.
However, the Ministry is not afraid that hundreds of thousands of unlicensed drivers will be on the road.
