In parallel with its parliamentary formality, which ended today with the vote of Congress of the amendments incorporated into the bill in the Senate, the Government submitted to a public hearing the regulation that will develop the new law, with the aim of its entry into force before the year ends.
The representatives of the various groups agreed to highlight the effort made by MPs and Senators to negotiate and agree on the best regulations to guarantee investor protection and to regulate in detail the activities of the bodies so that markets function effectively.
Mifid, which amends the Securities Market Law, involves the modernization of financial markets, at a time when it strengthens investor protection, improves the powers of the leaders of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and promotes cooperation between the various leaders of the European Union.
The new regulation will make it possible to provide financial advisory services to specialist company names as well as to natural or legal persons and creates a new type of financial services (ESIS), financial consulting firms (AFIs), which merge with securities companies, securities agencies and portfolio management companies.
In addition, it increases the number of systems for the execution of transactions in financial instruments, so that it is possible to add to the regulated secondary markets multilateral trading facilities and order internationalization systems, which compete with the current stock exchange managers.
The Law also obliges investment services firms to disclose on the market information on key aspects of its business profile, risk exposure and forms of risk management and requires them to keep a register of all transactions they carry out, to facilitate supervision by the CNMV.
