Which insurance is right for me?
Car insurance, which covers the driver in the event of possible losses, involves a significant expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, gender, age of the driver's license, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or the use made of it, among others.
Having a car is the main thing.
Y es que, escoger el seguro de automóvil adecuado es incluso más difícil que elegir el modelo de vehículo.
And it is that, choosing the right car insurance, is even more difficult than choosing the model of the vehicle.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurer.
This compromise takes the form of an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the premium granted and in exchange becomes responsible for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a claim.
The premium is the price of the insurance, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, age of the driver's license, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or use, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so that the higher the probability of an accident, the higher the rating to be paid.
It is for this reason that people over 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, since statistics show that these people have a lower claims rate due to their caution.
Similarly, using censuses, companies concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will influence the frequency, and therefore the probability of having an accident.
By increasing the frequency the probabilities increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the premium price.
This is why the driver must study the situation carefully to choose the car insurance that best suits his profile.
Here we will set out the most significant variables when choosing one or the other type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insurer, offers him a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 face various disadvantages when contracting with insurance at an affordable price, such as the lack of driving experience and the age of the driver's license.
Although the ideal way to be well insured is an all-risk insurance, other more economical options exist.
The most far-sighted drivers can opt for all-risk insurance with a deductible, so that they get the coverage of an all-risk insurance but at a more affordable price.
This form of agreement implies that the customer pays part of the amount of the claim.
"The part of the amount of the claim that the customer pays will be established according to the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount," says Luis Noguera, the head of First Europa, an online insurance mediator in Spain.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer provides protection to deal with damage caused to third parties, but by those caused on his own car.
In addition, it would be covered against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
A word of advice.
If you are under 25 years of age, try to be careful and avoid losses as much as possible, as this will affect the bonus, which may reduce the price of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction in the base rate owned by the company.
On the contrary, a penalty is an increase in the basic tariff.
"Bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and its profit.
If the company has had a good year it can afford to increase the bonuses, "clarifies Noguera.
Beyond the age of 25 it becomes easier for drivers when signing a contract with insurance, since the claims rate is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
It is for this reason that it is preferable to choose an all-risk insurance with deductible.
"Normally young people cannot benefit from the experience gained beforehand after an accident," says the director of the European company in Spain and adds that the majority of accidents occur during the second year of driving, once past the "fear of the novice".
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is preferable for him to negotiate insurance at all risks, as long as his economic situation allows it.
Marriages with children are considered by insurers to be the people with the lowest claims ratio, because the mark-ups will be lower.
In this case the best insurance would be an all-risk insurance with deductible (which can be 300 euros), or an extended third-party insurance from the third year of life of the vehicle when the insured has a high level of bonus.
"They have a more relaxed driving style and they have more purchasing power to afford the luxury of taking on a larger amount of franchises," Noguera said.
For retirees an all-risk insurance with deductible is preferable (being this one of 150 euros), or an extended third-party insurance when the insurer has a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver in the event of possible losses, but also because it represents a significant expense, which is why it is fundamental to properly study the insurance that suits us most according to our personal situation.
