The new gas deal between Russia and Ukraine is sounding the alarm.
A dispute over the price of gas is brewing between Ukraine and Russia, increasing the risk of repercussions on fuel exports to Europe.
Most Russian gas exports to the European Union (EU) are conveyed by pipelines, and every pipeline is scrupulously monitored.
