Richard Gere is simply not cynical enough.
With "The Hunting Party" and "Deadly Peace", two films once again address the Balkan war.
But both are not convincing.
Either the projects rely too much on action and senseless exchanges of fire or, on the contrary, they are too tearful.
Here, even Richard Gere in "The Hunting Party" can't help.
